when who comes
rattling down the ward

1872
01:28:27,062 --> 01:28:31,192
with his bedpans
but Leslie Jackson.

1873
01:28:31,266 --> 01:28:32,198
He killed him?

1874
01:28:32,267 --> 01:28:33,962
No, no, no.

1875
01:28:34,036 --> 01:28:38,302
No, no, I reckon
he tries to help him.

1876
01:28:38,374 --> 01:28:41,104
Says he'll get him
out of the hospital.

1877
01:28:41,176 --> 01:28:43,872
Find him a private doctor.

1878
01:28:48,183 --> 01:28:49,616
But of course,

1879
01:28:49,685 --> 01:28:51,050
once Priest
leaves the hospital,

1880
01:28:51,120 --> 01:28:52,644
he's finished.

1881
01:28:52,721 --> 01:28:54,689
He's too far gone.

1882
01:28:57,626 --> 01:29:00,754
Leslie Jackson
finds out about that,

1883
01:29:00,829 --> 01:29:04,993
and there's only one
way to keep it quiet.

1884
01:29:16,011 --> 01:29:17,205
Come on, man!

1885
01:29:17,279 --> 01:29:20,942
Don't die on me now!

1886
01:29:21,016 --> 01:29:23,211
Jesus!

1887
01:29:48,277 --> 01:29:51,405
But you don't know that?

1888
01:29:51,480 --> 01:29:56,179
I know that
I don't know that.

1889
01:29:56,251 --> 01:29:58,219
I can guess it though.

1890
01:29:58,287 --> 01:30:01,256
And then a year later someone
kills Lester Bryce-Jones

1891
01:30:01,323 --> 01:30:03,086
and one thing
leads to another?

1892
01:30:03,158 --> 01:30:05,922
Yes, I hope so.

1893
01:30:07,729 --> 01:30:09,424
Who then?

1894
01:30:09,498 --> 01:30:11,591
That's what we've
got to find out.

1895
01:30:29,618 --> 01:30:30,846
Debbie?

1896
01:30:32,254 --> 01:30:34,085
I'll just be a moment.

1897
01:30:40,629 --> 01:30:42,563
I'm sorry, I can't...

1898
01:30:43,465 --> 01:30:44,489
Not you again?

1899
01:30:44,566 --> 01:30:47,558
Mmm, I was just having a
look at my astral chart.

1900
01:30:47,636 --> 01:30:50,104
Trouble is I can't remember
what my star sign is.

1901
01:30:50,172 --> 01:30:51,366
Look, I've got a client.

1902
01:30:51,440 --> 01:30:53,305
That's all right, go
ahead, don't mind me.

1903
01:30:53,375 --> 01:30:56,208
I only came in
looking for a painting.

1904
01:30:57,379 --> 01:30:59,244
Pamela, would you?

1905
01:31:03,752 --> 01:31:05,276
What painting?

1906
01:31:05,354 --> 01:31:09,984
A painting of a swimming
pool by David Hockney.

1907
01:31:10,058 --> 01:31:13,221
And what makes you
think it's here?

1908
01:31:13,295 --> 01:31:15,695
Because you tried to
sell it two days ago,

1909
01:31:15,764 --> 01:31:18,324
at the Ansty Galleries.

1910
01:31:18,400 --> 01:31:21,028
The attendant identified you.

1911
01:31:21,103 --> 01:31:22,832
Do you want to know how?

1912
01:31:22,905 --> 01:31:25,135
By your tattoo.

1913
01:31:28,076 --> 01:31:29,600
Well Mrs. Viner.

1914
01:31:29,678 --> 01:31:32,044
Do you want me to
get a search warrant?

1915
01:31:32,114 --> 01:31:34,776
Or will you just
show me where it is?

1916
01:31:54,937 --> 01:31:57,269
That painting we found in
your shop, Mrs. Viner,

1917
01:31:57,339 --> 01:31:58,499
it was stolen.

1918
01:31:58,574 --> 01:32:00,303
In a robbery
about eight years ago.

1919
01:32:00,375 --> 01:32:01,467
That's nothing to do with me.

1920
01:32:01,543 --> 01:32:03,408
I didn't know.

1921
01:32:03,478 --> 01:32:04,968
That's a pity.

1922
01:32:05,047 --> 01:32:07,845
You should always
ask about provenance.

1923
01:32:07,916 --> 01:32:10,612
Did you know that Leslie
dealt in stolen paintings.

1924
01:32:10,686 --> 01:32:12,654
No.

1925
01:32:12,721 --> 01:32:15,781
Look, that day he came
home with the Hockney.

1926
01:32:15,857 --> 01:32:18,724
He wanted someone
to help him sell it.

1927
01:32:18,794 --> 01:32:20,056
Oh, really?

1928
01:32:20,128 --> 01:32:21,254
And what time was this?

1929
01:32:21,330 --> 01:32:22,297
It was in the morning.

1930
01:32:22,364 --> 01:32:23,422
I saw him in the hall.

1931
01:32:23,498 --> 01:32:25,056
He asked you to help
him sell the painting?

1932
01:32:25,133 --> 01:32:26,566
What sort of help?

1933
01:32:26,635 --> 01:32:28,569
Oh, did I know any galleries?

1934
01:32:28,637 --> 01:32:31,333
Collectors who might
come to my studio?

1935
01:32:31,406 --> 01:32:33,237
And he gave it
to you, did he?

1936
01:32:33,308 --> 01:32:35,071
He just gave it you,
just like that?

1937
01:32:35,143 --> 01:32:36,405
Yes, he did.

1938
01:32:36,478 --> 01:32:38,878
No, he didn't!

1939
01:32:38,947 --> 01:32:40,471
Because your
daughter Leonie said

1940
01:32:40,549 --> 01:32:43,279
that she saw the
painting in his apartment

1941
01:32:43,352 --> 01:32:46,480
at 4:30 when she
came home from school.

1942
01:32:46,555 --> 01:32:48,489
You left and came back
again, didn't you?

1943
01:32:48,557 --> 01:32:49,581
Why would I?

1944
01:32:49,658 --> 01:32:52,092
Because you realized
Leslie had something
worth a small fortune

1945
01:32:52,160 --> 01:32:54,219
and you wanted
your share.

1946
01:32:54,296 --> 01:32:55,456
Only what you
didn't know was

1947
01:32:55,530 --> 01:32:56,690
that he couldn't get
rid of that painting

1948
01:32:56,765 --> 01:32:59,598
because it
was hot stuff.

1949
01:32:59,668 --> 01:33:03,502
It came from a murder scene.

1950
01:33:03,572 --> 01:33:05,597
I didn't go back.

1951
01:33:05,674 --> 01:33:07,335
You had a key to the door.

1952
01:33:07,409 --> 01:33:10,105
You had the opportunity,
the motive and the will.

1953
01:33:10,178 --> 01:33:12,271
Do you know what I think?

1954
01:33:12,347 --> 01:33:14,975
I think that you and
Lester Bryce-Jones

1955
01:33:15,050 --> 01:33:17,746
were running a
nice little racket.

1956
01:33:17,819 --> 01:33:21,983
Clients at your studio
could buy paintings

1957
01:33:22,057 --> 01:33:23,854
with no questions asked.

1958
01:33:23,925 --> 01:33:25,790
And then you and
Leslie or Lester

1959
01:33:25,861 --> 01:33:27,988
or whatever his
ruddy name was

1960
01:33:28,063 --> 01:33:29,928
could split the proceeds.

1961
01:33:29,998 --> 01:33:31,625
Sorry, no way.

1962
01:33:31,700 --> 01:33:34,191
Oh yes.

1963
01:33:34,269 --> 01:33:38,228
But this time he wasn't
playing ball, was he?

1964
01:33:38,306 --> 01:33:41,036
So I think that you went
to have it out with him.

1965
01:33:41,109 --> 01:33:43,270
When you knocked at the
door and go no answer,

1966
01:33:43,345 --> 01:33:47,179
you used your key
to let yourself in.

1967
01:33:47,249 --> 01:33:49,410
And when you went in

1968
01:33:49,484 --> 01:33:53,477
you found Leslie up
to some deviant trick,

1969
01:33:53,555 --> 01:33:55,614
probably high
on painkillers

1970
01:33:55,691 --> 01:33:58,319
but certainly not in
a position to argue.

1971
01:33:58,393 --> 01:34:01,829
I don't believe this.

1972
01:34:01,897 --> 01:34:04,957
And then you tightened
the belt around his neck,

1973
01:34:05,033 --> 01:34:07,593
just to make sure.

1974
01:34:07,669 --> 01:34:09,762
Then you opened
the doors to the patio

1975
01:34:09,838 --> 01:34:12,068
so it looked as though
someone came in that way.

1976
01:34:12,140 --> 01:34:14,438
You returned the
key to your apartment

1977
01:34:14,509 --> 01:34:18,240
then you took the
painting to your studio.

1978
01:34:18,313 --> 01:34:21,043
Mrs. Viner, I believe
that you are responsible

1979
01:34:21,116 --> 01:34:23,380
for the murder
of Leslie Jackson,

1980
01:34:23,452 --> 01:34:25,818
alias Lester Bryce-Jones.

1981
01:34:25,887 --> 01:34:26,911
No, it wasn't like that.

1982
01:34:26,988 --> 01:34:28,114
He was unconscious.

1983
01:34:28,190 --> 01:34:28,918
(Knock on door)

1984
01:34:28,990 --> 01:34:29,957
Yes?

1985
01:34:32,761 --> 01:34:33,955
DC Jordan has
entered the room

1986
01:34:34,029 --> 01:34:36,156
with a note for DI Frost.

1987
01:34:53,982 --> 01:34:55,142
So he was dying

1988
01:34:55,217 --> 01:34:58,015
and you offered
him no assistance?

1989
01:35:02,491 --> 01:35:05,016
I took the painting.

1990
01:35:05,093 --> 01:35:06,287
I was strapped for money.

1991
01:35:06,361 --> 01:35:07,589
The studio earns nothing.

1992
01:35:07,662 --> 01:35:09,596
There are
Leonie's school fees.

1993
01:35:12,701 --> 01:35:13,929
I'd helped him before.

1994
01:35:14,002 --> 01:35:15,697
Not that I liked him.

1995
01:35:15,771 --> 01:35:17,295
Fact is he made
my skin crawl,

1996
01:35:17,372 --> 01:35:19,567
but the money was useful.

1997
01:35:19,641 --> 01:35:21,108
Except this time he
was cutting me out.

1998
01:35:21,176 --> 01:35:22,370
And as soon as
I saw that picture

1999
01:35:22,444 --> 01:35:25,106
I knew what it was.

2000
01:35:25,180 --> 01:35:27,114
But it wasn't.

2001
01:35:27,182 --> 01:35:28,877
What do you mean?

2002
01:35:28,950 --> 01:35:33,478
It was a forgery.

2003
01:35:33,555 --> 01:35:36,547
The painting wasn't genuine.

2004
01:36:01,216 --> 01:36:04,049
Morning Mullett.

2005
01:36:04,119 --> 01:36:05,552
Morning, sir.

2006
01:36:05,620 --> 01:36:07,417
A word in your ear.

2007
01:36:26,474 --> 01:36:28,135
I'm really sorry, sir.

2008
01:36:30,345 --> 01:36:32,870
Yes.

2009
01:36:32,948 --> 01:36:35,314
I think everyone
will be really sorry.

2010
01:36:39,221 --> 01:36:40,654
Yes.

2011
01:36:42,257 --> 01:36:46,626
Especially Mrs. Mullett.

2012
01:36:46,695 --> 01:36:50,756
Especially Mrs. Mullett.

2013
01:36:50,832 --> 01:36:53,801
Did they give you a reason?

2014
01:36:53,869 --> 01:36:57,635
Yes, they gave me a reason.

2015
01:36:57,706 --> 01:36:58,604
There was another candidate

2016
01:36:58,673 --> 01:37:01,369
that some of the
board preferred.

2017
01:37:01,443 --> 01:37:05,345
A woman Super
from Northumberland,

2018
01:37:05,413 --> 01:37:07,381
very strong on management.

2019
01:37:07,449 --> 01:37:11,909
Oh, well, you can't
blame yourself then.

2020
01:37:11,987 --> 01:37:15,184
No, I can't.

2021
01:37:15,257 --> 01:37:17,282
I can blame...

2022
01:37:22,264 --> 01:37:23,731
Who?

2023
01:37:23,798 --> 01:37:25,197
I don't know how you
could do it to me, Jack.

2024
01:37:25,267 --> 01:37:27,758
You can't blame me, I did
everything that you asked.

2025
01:37:27,836 --> 01:37:29,235
I cleared up my three cases.

2026
01:37:29,304 --> 01:37:30,566
I did my expenses.

2027
01:37:30,639 --> 01:37:33,073
Yes, that was what did it.

2028
01:37:33,141 --> 01:37:35,268
What?

2029
01:37:35,343 --> 01:37:37,174
It seems I foolishly failed

2030
01:37:37,245 --> 01:37:39,975
to check your paperwork.

2031
01:37:40,048 --> 01:37:42,744
You signed those petrol
receipts yourself didn't you?

2032
01:37:42,817 --> 01:37:45,945
Forged the signatures.

2033
01:37:46,021 --> 01:37:52,153
As someone on the board
was very quick to point out.

2034
01:37:52,227 --> 01:37:53,717
Yeah, well, I mean,
I didn't think that...

2035
01:37:53,795 --> 01:37:56,286
No, you didn't, did you?

2036
01:38:14,049 --> 01:38:16,210
My resignation.

2037
01:38:28,063 --> 01:38:32,466
Just get out of
my office, Jack.

2038
01:38:32,534 --> 01:38:34,627
Go on, get out!

2039
01:39:04,899 --> 01:39:06,560
Brian, are you there?

2040
01:39:14,676 --> 01:39:16,268
Mr. Frost.

2041
01:39:16,344 --> 01:39:17,572
Ah.

2042
01:39:18,646 --> 01:39:19,908
On your way?

2043
01:39:19,981 --> 01:39:21,209
Yes, yes, I am.

2044
01:39:21,282 --> 01:39:24,080
I'm moving into
my new house.

2045
01:39:24,152 --> 01:39:28,248
Well, it's my
old house actually.

2046
01:39:28,323 --> 01:39:29,449
Got to start learning

2047
01:39:29,524 --> 01:39:32,220
how to be a domestic
animal once again.

2048
01:39:32,293 --> 01:39:33,851
You should get
yourself a cat.

2049
01:39:33,928 --> 01:39:35,828
Well, me, no.

2050
01:39:35,897 --> 01:39:37,159
Can't stand them.

2051
01:39:40,101 --> 01:39:43,867
Anyway, we shall
miss you, Mr. Frost.

2052
01:39:43,938 --> 01:39:46,736
Well, I'll miss
you too, Brian.

2053
01:39:46,808 --> 01:39:49,470
You've been a great support.

2054
01:39:49,544 --> 01:39:50,943
And Donald.

2055
01:39:51,012 --> 01:39:51,774
Is he here?

2056
01:39:51,846 --> 01:39:52,870
I never did get to...

2057
01:39:52,947 --> 01:39:56,110
I'll tell you a
little secret, Mr. Frost.

2058
01:39:56,184 --> 01:39:58,118
There is no Donald.

2059
01:39:58,186 --> 01:40:00,177
It's all just me.

2060
01:40:00,255 --> 01:40:02,849
Donald left three months ago.

2061
01:40:12,267 --> 01:40:15,134
Goodbye, Brian.

2062
01:40:15,203 --> 01:40:17,137
Jack.

